				<title>[Tuyển] System Operator, Security Officer</title>
				<description><![CDATA[ Cty mình đang có nhu cầu tuyển dụng các vị trí trên, anh em cảm thấy phù hợp thì gởi CV cho mình qua email hoặc PM hen.

E-mail: profbkhn at gmail dot com.

Cảm ơn mọi người.

1) Vị trí cần tuyển: <b>System Operator</b>

<b>Job Descriptions:</b>
•	Responsible daily system, servers & network operations and administration task activity.
•	To support, monitor, test and troubleshoot online services system, software and software applications issues.
•	Responsible to monitor and support the servers availability and stability.
•	Perform and monitor the backup and restore as per schedule or request.
•	Perform and monitor system schedule job to ensure it is completed successfully.
•	Ensure availability of infrastructure connectivity by using monitoring tools effectively.
•	Perform daily checklist to minimize system downtime and ensure business continuity.
•	Ensure immediate and proper escalation and notification of unresolved problems / failures to appropriate parties (2nd level of support) for prompt remedial action.
•	To ensure appropriate process standards are met and maintained.

<b>Requirements:</b>
•	At least Diploma/Degree in Computer Science/Information Technology or equivalent.
•	Good knowledge of local area network (LAN) and WAN/Network environment.
•	Familiarity with Windows 2003 Server & Linux platform (LAMP) with good troubleshooting skills and knowledge of Windows/*nix-based OS, networking, web-based infrastructure and hardware issues are essential. 
•	Comfortable to work with minimal supervision, have the ability to work in a team environment and consistently demonstrate initiative. 
•	Willingness to work in rotating schedules.

<b>Salary:</b> Negotiable

==========

2) Vị trí cần tuyển: <b>IT Security Officer</b> 

<b>Job Descriptions:</b>
•	Installation and configuration of security softwares/equipment (IDS, Firewall).
•	Maintaining network security, platform security (e.g. Windows, Linux).
•	Work closely with IT sections on corporate technology developments to fully secure information, computers, network and processing systems. 
•	Remain informed on trends and issues in the security industry, including current and emerging technologies.
•	Coordinating requests for penetration test (assess network or server vulnerabilities) and application security test (assess web application vulnerabilities)

<b>Requirements:</b>
•	At least Diploma/Degree in Computer Science/Information Technology or equivalent.
•	Good knowledge of local area network (LAN) and WAN/Network environment.
•	Familiarity with Windows 2003 Server & Linux platform (LAMP) and knowledge of Windows/*nix-based OS, networking, web-based infrastructure are essential. 
•	Comfortable to work with minimal supervision, have the ability to work in a team environment and consistently demonstrate initiative. 
•	Ability to multi-task.
•	Good system programming/troubleshooting is a plus.
•	Good knowledge of online services system/infrastructure is a plus.

<b>Salary:</b> Negotiable]]></description>
